Library Management Requirements

1. Any library member should be able to search book by thier title, author, subject category and date of publication.
2. Each book will have a unique identification number and other details including a rack number which will help to physically locate the book.
3. There could be more than one copy of book, and library member should be able to check-out and reserve any copy. We will call each copy of a book, a book item.
4. The system should be able to retrive information like who took a particular book or what are the book checked out by a specific library member.
5. There should be a maximum limit 5 on how many book a member could check out.
6. There should be a maximum limit 10 days a member can keep the book.
7. The system should be able to collect fines for books returned after the due date.
8. Members should be able to reserve books that are not currently available.
9. The system should be able to send notifications whenever the reserved books become available as well as book is not returned in due date.
10. Each book and member card will have a unique bar code. The system will be able to read barcode from the boos and members library cards.


Actors :

1. Librarian
2. Customer
3. System/Server

Use Cases : 

Here are the top use cases of Library Management System

1. Add/Remove/Edit Book 
2. Search Book 
3. Send Notification
4. Issue a book
5. Reserve a book
6. Renew a book
7. Return a book